INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(70893, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'When everyone works together, the soup tastes GREAT!\n\nYou should try some when it\'s ready to eat!', 47213), -- Community Feast
(70959, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do you love animals?\n\nOf course you do, who doesn\'t? Even the scary ones are pretty neat!\n\nYou wanna take care of one of the animals I tamed all by myself? I can tame more if you wanna trade for them, too--as long as you promise to take good care of them!', 47213), -- Cute and Cuddly
(72291, 432, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What\'s that? You have a story for me? Sit down, let me hear it!\n\n<Elder Poa listens to your tale of a victory over a peculiar foe.>\n\nThat was thrilling! Thank you for sharing that with me, young one.', 47213), -- Story of a Memorable Victory
(72584, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. Don\'t forget to pick up your fishing net in a few hours. We don\'t want the fish to go to waste!', 47213), -- Setting Your Very Own Net
(70701, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We must be vigilant about our livestock. We are limited in resources to begin with. To lose an argali is a setback we would much like to avoid.', 47213), -- Bakar Dream of Lost Argali
(67605, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work. Yours will be a tale to be told to our next generation of hunters.', 47213), -- Thundering Plains
(70210, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I owe you much. It is hard to ask an outsider for help with something so important to our clan, but I do not see another option.', 47213), -- Tradition Not Forgotten
(65798, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ancestors forgive me. If I were stronger, we would not need to resort to such a questionable method for resources.', 47213), -- An Opportunistic Approach
(70820, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ach! I thought a lifetime of gryphon wrangling would have prepared me for taming the unruly beasts of the Dragon Isles. But these Marmoni and Skitterbugs are pushing me to my limits! I will gladly offload one to you. If you seek another, I\'ll offer ye a fair trade!', 47213), -- The Basecamp 'Pets'
(65486, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Akunda flips through the photographs quickly, intently analyzing each one.>\n\nRe-mark-a-ble! Surprisin\' too. I\'ve much to learn from these; so many new specimens to document!\n\nThank you, $n!', 47213), -- Picture Perfect
(69870, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope ya brought ya swim trunks. This river be lively!', 47213), -- Pictures with Purpose
(72525, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, your new camera is beautiful. It matches you perfectly!', 47213), -- Basic Cataloging Gear
(70058, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, yes! These materials should be plenty to repair your Happy Duck, young one.\n\n<Mahra smiles at you.>\n\nThank you for bringing this important matter to my attention, $n. It should only take me a moment.', 47213), -- Friend on the Mend
(69898, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, wow! That\'s the most delicious-looking meat I\'ve EVER seen! My project will get the BEST grade. The proto-whelp will definitely want this!\n\n<Iyali\'s expression is suddenly filled with concern.>\n\nOh no! \n\nI mean, uh, everyone will lwant to copy me... for the project!\n\n<Iyali smiles unconvincingly.>', 47213), -- Scientific Meat-thod
(69897, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, some proto-whelps like to be petted, but some don\'t? \n\nThat\'s not good. What if this one calls its friends? Or what if it\'s mean? \n\nI mean, this lesson, uh, makes no sense! This, uh, homework is very difficult. \n\nThank you for helping me. I\'m sorry if you got hurt...', 47213), -- Behavior Analysis "Homework"
(67047, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah! This is most certainly the Coldsnap Sagittate! My nostrils are exhilarated! \n\nExcellent work, $n! I am positive our venerable guests will be gargling your praises with each sip of warmth imbibed. Let us not forget to do so with some of these delicious little cakes Morsel and Flemthroat made as well!', 47213), -- Warm Away These Shivers
(70888, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Working day and night to outfit our forces is no small feat. It\'s arduous work, but I enjoy it. And I hear you have been a boon to our efforts. \n\nAs a show of thanks, I want you to take one of my armor pieces. Just one. If you require another, I will want something in trade.\n\nMake your choice quickly. I have work to do!', 47213), -- Rubbing Shoulders With The Best
(66942, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve been told that the Primalists reject civilization and seek to bring about its downfall. Ha! The joke is on them. Their rituals will inspire dozens of new gizmos that will bring about the next technological golden age.', 47213), -- -Unknown-
(66006, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have the supplies? Good.\n\nLeave them by the forge.\n\n<Roscha looks around and frowns.>', 47213), -- Return to Roscha
(70319, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you. With these reagents I should be able to stop the infection from spreading, then hopefully clear it completely. I owe you a life-debt.\n\nBe wary of Negazurai, traveler. His thirst for blood is unyielding.', 47213), -- Nergazurai
(65949, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Is this... ah. It is. My beloved is in the sky, then, running with Ohn\'ahra. I will join her... in time.\n\nThank you, $p. \n\nI will remember what you have done for Clan Shikaar. And for me.', 47213), -- The Sole Mender
(66005, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This medallion is all that remains of a dear friend of mine who ventured too far into the swamp this past season. I thought it lost to the elements.\n\nI cut this leather from her first mammoth hunt. We were children, then.', 47213), -- Medallion of a Fallen Friend
(65952, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With their chieftain slain, the gorlocs will no longer bother us. \n\nI am astounded by how strong they became under Chief Grrlgllmesh. \n\nI have never seen such primitive creatures rise up against a mighty civilization like ours before. Are we not so different? So much further evolved? I suppose not...', 47213), -- A Chief of Legends
(65954, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Magnificent beasts, aren\'t they?\n\nEvery bakar holds a special place in Clan Shikaar. They are our fellow hunters, guards, and our most cherished friends.', 47213), -- Release the Hounds
(65955, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $p. We are safe in here and can speak freely. \n\nI will protect Baba from any gorlocs that dare venture in while he rests.', 47213), -- A Centaur's Best Friend
(65953, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Khasar frowns at the totems.>\n\nThese totems are for storm magic. Storm magic is sacrilege to the gift of winds given by Ohn\'ahra herself.\n\nI will deliver these to the mystics.', 47213), -- The Ora-cull
(65950, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Roscha sent you? She must be furious.\n\nShe has been through so much already. I could not return without securing all that was lost.', 47213), -- Thieving Gorlocs
(65951, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $p. Let\'s get to work.', 47213), -- Sole Supplier
(66684, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve returned! I felt the destruction of the source from here.', 47213), -- Storm Chasing
(65836, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'No!', 47213), -- Show of Storm
(66683, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Watu stares at shock at his leg, newly bloody and pierced with the shard.>', 47213), -- Last Resort Analysis
(66689, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Watu doesn\'t register your presence. He remains sitting, favoring the injured leg, and has his eyes closed.>', 47213), -- More Than A Rock
(66680, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So our argali live. Give Wish an extra pat for me, will you? I would do it myself, but I can\'t move. <Watu sighs.>', 47213), -- Counting Sheep
(66681, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The pines should be a little safer now.', 47213), -- Tempests Abound
(71028, 378, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'May the winds of Ohn\'ahra guide and protect you.\n\nReturn when your renown grows, and I will train you further.', 47213), -- Hunting Tactics: Blessing of Ohn'ahra
(66011, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Theramus looks quietly upon the newly restored shrine.>', 47213), -- In Memory of Ysera
(65904, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '...I think it worked? He left the cave!', 47213), -- Enough Is Enough
(65937, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve returned!', 47213), -- Proof of Negligence
(65905, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $r.', 47213), -- More Than Weeds
(65902, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh dear. We heard his outburst. Are you okay?', 47213), -- Food or Floof
(65900, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The meat to sourbloom ratio is just right.', 47213), -- Suspiciously Spiced Steak
(65903, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So! Many! Hoppers! Let\'s pet them all!', 47213), -- Can't Beat Fluffy
(65899, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found him! It looks like he\'s really down in the dumps today.', 47213), -- Find Theramus
(66834, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Rellen established the centaur\'s footing in these plains. We would have never survived without his teachings.', 47213), -- Rellen, the Learned
(71027, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mara\'nar has been slain. May his kin learn to stay within their own lands.', 47213), -- WANTED: Mara'nar the Thunderous
(70374, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you have witnessed Himia, the Blessed.', 47213), -- Himia, the Blessed
(66687, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve returned intact. Good. Always respect the animals\' prowess.', 47213), -- Land of the Apex
(66688, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<There are ashen remains of previously offered wind tokens in the iron container.>\n\n<You place what you\'ve gathered on top.>', 47213), -- Signs of the Wind
(67039, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They all returned before you. Thank the winds!', 47213), -- An Amazing Journey
(67034, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These reagents will be used to initiate new members into our tribe. I will repay this debt.', 47213), -- Of Wind and Water
(70279, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Admirable work! You match the prowess of Teerai\'s finest hunters.', 47213), -- Blood of Dragons
(70990, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will get this wool to the artisans who can use it. Thank you.', 47213), -- If There's Wool There's a Way
(69981, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh no! Bless their soul... <Mahra looks over the equipment.>\n\nIt\'s all ruined. Spent too long in the elements. \n\nHere, take this and craft some new armor. Or speak with one of the Crafting Orders clerks next to me or in Valdrakken and have someone do it for you. I suggest something for your wrists or chest.\n\nOne other thing. The quality of these reagents isn\'t great, but you can always have your new equipment recrafted later to raise its quality.', 47213), -- Customer Satisfaction
(69915, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, thank you, thank you! You\'re the best $p!', 47213), -- Targeted Ads
(66597, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 'A what symbol!? That can\'t be right...\n\n<Thaelin scratches his beard.>\n\nThere\'s only one way to find out.', 47213), -- This Old Stone
(66595, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Message? What message?\n\nWhat do ye mean it vanished mysteriously?\n\nWell, no matter. We\'ve got much to discuss.', 47213), -- Dormant Discovery
(69869, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There are incredible new specimens to catalog everywhere you look!', 47213), -- A Cataloger's Paradise
(70808, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dragons have long fascinated me. Being here is a dream come true! I have already learned much about the renewed proto-drakes of the Waking Shores. Would you like to see one of the manuscripts I have put together? I have made many observations, and would be willing to trade for others as well!', 47213), -- Initial Mysteries of the Dragon Isles Drakes
(70807, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We appreciate your continued help with the expedition! As a reward for your efforts, I want to offer you one of my advanced tools. I have all of these tools available for trade, so come and see me again if you\'d like another.\n\nThank you, adventurer!', 47213), -- Advanced Excavation Tools
(70828, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These lands are vast--the terrain rises so much that it\'s easy for even the most knowledgeable tracker to get lost. If you want to help us out, you\'ll need a way to navigate. Take this compass, it should do the trick.', 47213), -- Wayfinder's Compass
(71005, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ooo, I love puzzles! I should ask the archivists if I can help with putting these back together!\n\nI\'ll ensure this is properly documented, researched, and archived for the expedition.', 47213), -- -Unknown-
(66529, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Someday, I hope to fight for my people with the same bravery as this proto-dragon in its final moments.\n\nThanks again, $n.', 47213), -- A Thousand Words
(66528, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, a fight to the death with something just as strong? I wonder if it was protecting the preserve from invaders?\n\nThank you, $n. It\'s good to remember the sacrifices of those that have come before us.', 47213), -- King Without a Crown
(66527, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So totally unrelated, but you didn\'t see another camera up there, did you?\n\nYou know what? Forget I said anything.', 47213), -- Professional Protography
(66525, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, look at that! The colors came through beautifully. Looks like you\'re a pretty good cataloger already!', 47213), -- Competitive Protography
(66526, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. The Primalists remain a threat, but these dragons enjoy their freedom once again.', 47213), -- Preserving the Wilds
(66846, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is it! I have never seen such a card before! Such power! So many possibilities!\n\nMagnificent!\n\nThank you, $n. Now I am ready...', 47213), -- The Heart of the Deck
(66845, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The apparition explained itself and asked for forgiveness.\n\nBut then they asked to play a single match with me. \n\nOur game is apparently very different from what they used to play, and they wanted to try it.\n\nThank you for helping both of us. Maybe the match will be fun?', 47213), -- Legendary Foil
(66840, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A deep wyrm?\n\nSomething must have driven it away from its underground nest. Whatever spooked this apex predator  must be very terrible indeed.\n\nThank you, $p, I will make sure to remove the carcass it doesn\'t contaminate the water.', 47213), -- Water Safety
(66841, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is an unbelievable find! I have never seen ancient pottery like this. And these markings... Give me a moment while I inspect them.', 47213), -- A Shard of the Past
(66843, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank ye for findin\' him. Betcha he won\'t stray far alone anymore.\n\nHere\'s a little somethin\' for ye help.', 47213), -- Out of Lukh
(66839, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, these are be-u-ti-ful! This one is spicy! And this one reminds me of Earthroot. Oh, I can taste the sweet mead now...\n\nThank ye kindly, friend! Ye saved me and the gang\'s afternoon!', 47213), -- It's Brew Time!
(66844, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, it be a sad time for me, but it had to be done. \n\nHere, take one of Shokhari\'s kits. I can\'t keep dem all. Carin\' for dem be the least we can do. \n\nRaise it well.', 47213), -- The Great Shokhari
(66838, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh! These are awesome. So luxurious and soft...\n\nNow, only if Valdo were here to clean them up!', 47213), -- It's Cold Up Here
(66837, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks to you--and no thanks to Valdo--I can feed all these hungry travelers!\n\nHmm... are you looking for a job? I\'ve got a recent \"opening\"...\n\nCan\'t pay you much, but you can have Valdo\'s spot! No? Ah well, can\'t blame me for trying.', 47213), -- Nothing for Breakfast
(66232, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is will go a long way in helping us in these parts. We just might let your friends stick around...', 47213), -- Afront 'Till A Salt
(66559, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It appears you\'ve managed to return our dwarf. And in a single piece, no less. On behalf of both our team and the Dragonscale Expedition, I thank you. \n\nWe\'ll get Mordigan some fluids, then start packing up. \n\nThere\'s nothing in these hills save blood and salt.', 47213), -- Back To Camp
(66187, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'An inelegant solution, but I appreciate your quick thinking and... resourcefulness.', 47213), -- Mad Mordigan & The Crystal King
(66177, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve been busy. So have I.', 47213), -- No Dwarf Left Behind
(66175, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They say to expect the unexpected, but wow... this is unprecedented!', 47213), -- Field Experiment
(66164, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re back! I\'ll start getting the Geoscanner 289-07 reconfigured and as functional as circumstances allow. These seaside conditions are admittedly less than ideal.', 47213), -- Fishy Fingers
(66147, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work! I\'ll get this to LOU-C and see what her little contraption can make of it.', 47213), -- Crystals in the Water
(66154, 742, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, what do you know? Someone around here actually accomplished something. What\'s that old saying? Two for you, one for me?\n\n<Rowe takes a small sip from the beaker.>\n\nAh, that\'s the stuff.', 47213), -- Salivatory Samples
(66781, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect! Prepare to witness the most impressive feat o\' geology ye\'ve ever seen!', 47213), -- A Matter of Taste
(71234, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Another one?\n\nOh joy.', 47213), -- Nook News
(66155, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Phew, what a ride! It\'s a miracle the boat is in one piece!\n\nThank you very much, $n. Let us meet again for another ride!', 47213), -- Ruriq's River Rapids Ride
(65930, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With how much older he is, Kauj has always been almost... more a father than a brother. \n\nI thought getting older and starting my own family would make me feel less like I needed him. \n\nI was wrong. Even before my wife passed, I was wrong.', 47213), -- A Wrestle of Wind and Water
(65929, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. Otu\'rorq, the local River Spirit, will be pleased to know his river will continue to flow, for now.', 47213), -- Ice Breakers
(65928, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will tend to these motes, so they dissipate harmlessly. Kraunot will be pleased.', 47213), -- Wayward Winds
(66724, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did you hear all that, hero?', 47213), -- The Gleamfisher
(65926, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ruriq is as stubborn as ever.', 47213), -- Tackling the Falls
(65925, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s a pity to wipe out any natural life... even troublesome ones.', 47213), -- Culling the Cullers
(65914, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With these remains, I think we can make something truly special... something that will put the souls of the mammoths at ease.', 47213), -- Mammoths Matter
(70338, 378, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that Sylvie is healing, these kits will be in good hands...\n\nEr, paws...\n\nClaws?', 47213), -- They Took the Kits
(69862, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s faint, but I can hear what sounds like kits in the cave!\n\nThis is bad...', 47213), -- Save a Slyvern
(68644, 378, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve healed her, but she is clearly still in distress.\n\nHm, I wonder if...', 47213), -- Sugar, Spice, and Everything Nice
(68642, 412, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. You didn\'t hurt yourself on the crystalpine, right?', 47213), -- Needles to Say
(68643, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent, $n. \n\nThese samples should give us a more complete picture of how the outbreak is spreading.', 47213), -- Vitamins and Minerals
(68641, 378, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh! Thank you so much, $n!\n\nI may be a mage, but sometimes natural solutions are the most effective.', 47213), -- Mossing the Mark
(68639, 483, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<She scribbles notes down in her journal.>\n\nYes... Yes, this is all very helpful. Hopefully the Kirin Tor will be able to use this information to help others afflicted by the arcane sickness.', 47213), -- Prowling Polar Predators
(70970, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'To\'tik was right. This place is cursed. \n\nWe\'ll let the Kirin Tor know what happened here, $n. Thank you for your help. \n\nThis is a lesson I won\'t soon forget...', 47213), -- Good Intentions
(70946, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is worse than I thought. Way worse.', 47213), -- No One May Wield It
(70931, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. With this many shards, I\'ll be able to easily locate the artifact.', 47213), -- Whispered Fragments
(70937, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let\'s see what you\'ve found...', 47213), -- What Valthrux Once Was
(70859, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Give it to me! Quickly now!\n\nDid you hear the whispers too?', 47213), -- What the Guardian Beholds
(70858, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have my thanks... I thought I would die before acquiring this artifact.', 47213), -- Back into the Action
(70856, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work. This should give us some breathing room.', 47213), -- Kill it with Fire
(67724, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great! This spider silk will burn for a long time.', 47213), -- The Fending Flames
(67111, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, wonderful! With these venom glands, I can brew an antidote for Alia. She\'ll be feeling better in no time at all.', 47213), -- The Ailing Apprentice
(66270, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They\'re just going to keep fighting until they find a new leader? That settles it then. If I\'m ever going to have a base of operations here, we\'ll have to kill all of them.\n\nThe plan is that we...\n\nWait, you\'re leaving? You don\'t want any part of this? What am I going to do? I can\'t leave this lake now that I\'ve made an enemy of the gnolls!\n\nFine! Side with those flea-bitten miscreants!\n\nTake what I promised and go. You\'re not the only \"champion\" in these woods! I\'ll find someone else to help me!', 47213), -- Whack-a-Gnoll
(66269, 604, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That had to work, right?', 47213), -- Just To Be Sure
(66268, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Finally! That has to be the last one. Right?', 47213), -- Third Try's the Charm
(66267, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'ll show those brutes!', 47213), -- M.E.T.A.
(66266, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Play dead, indeed!', 47213), -- Filthy Mongrels
(66265, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ha! Maybe next time they\'ll think twice before electing a new leader!', 47213), -- Who's Next?
(66264, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, those? Just dump them anywhere. I\'m sure the elementals won\'t mind.', 47213), -- Disarmed and Docile
(66263, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'How they must despair!', 47213), -- A Precision Approach
(66262, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can taste the difference already!', 47213), -- Waste Water Cleanup
(66261, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now, to work!', 47213), -- A Minor Setback
(71135, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let\'s never do this again.', 47213), -- Loose Ends
(71017, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<It\'s hard to tell, but you think you see a slight smile on Grimtusk\'s face. It quickly fades away.>\n\nThis will do.', 47213), -- Naluki's Letter
(71012, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There\'s Varsek. Guess he finally solved whatever puzzle he was after, eh?', 47213), -- Varsek Recruited
(71000, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Here\'s Barst. Just as... annoying as ever.', 47213), -- Barst Recruited
(71016, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Why, well aren\'t you just a fresh fish hopping out of the water! \n\nWhat\'s this? A letter from Grimtusk?', 47213), -- Grimtusk's Sister
(70954, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'While gnolls remain the primary focus of my research, I\'m very curious about the recently returned dragons as well. \n\nAfter intense study and observation, I began jotting down my notes on the subject. It\'s nowhere near complete, but when it is, I\'m sure it will be a helpful guide to you.\n\nIn the meantime, would you like to look at one of my other manuscripts? I\'ve started to trade them for items that will help continue my studies, so if you would like to learn more, visit me again!', 47213), -- Mounting Curiosity
(70943, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well now, you\'re a fast learner! Your fishing skills continue to improve.\n\nLet\'s see how you do with a spear. I\'ll craft for you your very first tuskarr harpoon. We shall see what you can land with it!\n\nI\'m sure you won\'t fail to impress.', 47213), -- Harpooning
(70996, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well I\'ll be! Guess I\'m heading out to help my pal Grimtusk after all!', 47213), -- A Little Kelp for My Friends
(71014, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, look at you! You made it all the way over here! How can I help you?', 47213), -- A Far Furbolg Friend
(71009, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh dear... I\'m not going to lie, $n, this isn\'t my proudest moment.', 47213), -- Elementary, My Dear Drakonid
(71015, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s very nice to meet you, but as you can see, I\'m a bit busy trying to solve this puzzle.', 47213), -- All Brawn, No Brains
(71013, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now you know what\'s at stake. \n\nTime to get moving.', 47213), -- No Vengeance on an Empty Stomach
(66730, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That wasn\'t so hard, was it?', 47213), -- True Survivors
(67050, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did WHAT!? Bah... doesn\'t matter for now. This isn\'t over just yet.', 47213), -- Frostbite: Causes and Symptoms
(66703, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So the sneaky shamans are dead?', 47213), -- Snowball Effect
(66715, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You smell like death... Frostbite likes that.', 47213), -- The Extraction
(66709, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Honestly? I thought your \"help\" would be the end of me.', 47213), -- Field Medic 101
(70550, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Once we have more control over the Cobalt Assembly, we\'ll be able to better support our allies in the fight against the Sundered Flame.', 47213), -- Welcome to the Assembly
(72784, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We could always use more aid. Allow me to tell you of our current situation.', 47213), -- Supporting the Cobalt Assembly
(66671, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Caddy sent ye? She wasn\'t here before all the commotion broke out with the tuskarr and the furbolg!\n\nTo say we got things to do in the camp is a wee understatement. We\'re flooded with problems!', 47213), -- Path to Nowhere
(66972, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This brings me no joy.\n\nBut I\'ll hang his tusk in a place of honor.\n\nThank you, $n.', 47213), -- Old Stonetusk
(66958, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent job, $p! This will go a long way in helping the bruffalon prosper and will hopefully show our Tuskarr neighbors we are also good stewards of this land.\n\nWe could learn a lesson from Bloodhorn. Just cause we\'re stomping through this beautiful place doesn\'t give us the right to do what we want with it!\n\nAlways leave the world better than you found it.', 47213), -- Protect And Herd
(66500, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Malygos and Sindragosa, huh? Never heard of \'em. Sounds like they were pretty in love though.\n\nI wonder who put these here?', 47213), -- Ways of Seeing
(66493, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done! Don\'t worry... it\'s the courier\'s fault if a parcel wasn\'t marked \"fragile.\"', 47213), -- Send It!
(66523, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $p. The embercones will burn hot. The elemental cores will temper the heat. And this leather... is fairly disgusting. But the bellows they produce will more than suffice!\n\nNow all I need is time.', 47213), -- Tending the Forge
(66489, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fantastic job! \n\nAfter repelling their attack on the camp, it\'s imperative that we keep the Primalists on the back foot. \n\nNow please give me my wand back.', 47213), -- Setting the Defense
(66488, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let us hope there aren\'t any more surprises trapped in that glacier.', 47213), -- WANTED: Frigellus
(69904, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The young vulpera nervously puts his hands behind his back.>\n\nDo we know you? Noriko said not to talk to strangers...', 47213), -- Suspiciously Quiet
(66213, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank goodness, a new story. \n\nLet\'s hear it!', 47213), -- The Weave of a Tale
(70942, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Greetings, friend! I see you\'re getting to know the ways of tuskarr, and thus the ways of the fish.\n\nIf you\'d like, I could make you something that will allow you to tackle fishing in the highland pools of the Dragon Isles. Think you\'re up for the challenge?', 47213), -- Highland Fishing
(70953, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Greetings, dear friend. \n\nYou\'ve been so kind to our community here in Iskaara. I have heard of your deeds and wanted to knit you something as a thanks.\n\nPlease, take your pick! I\'ve made many hats to while away the hours of the long winters. I would be happy to trade you for others as well, if you wish!', 47213), -- Tuskarr Headwear
(70936, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You there, young one! Our warriors take totems with them when they venture out into the Dragon Isles. Our totems are part of our livelihood--they are very important to us. Our enemies delight in taking them as trophies, and we can\'t let that happen! Please, return any totems you find.', 47213), -- Stolen Tuskarr Totems
(70940, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The deeds of the tuskarr of the Dragon Isles are many!\n\nOver the years though, some of our stories have been lost. Many travelers never returned from their journeys with tales to tell. \n\nPlease, if you find any scrolls that document what our lost brethren were able to accomplish, bring them back to me.', 47213), -- Tuskarr Champion's Tales
(70926, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah! Our totems are very important to us. You have our thanks for returning them, young one!', 47213), -- Stolen Totems
(66217, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is the cycle of the sea life out here. Some we leave to continue the line. Some we cull, some we eat. All in balance.', 47213), -- WANTED: Krojek the Shoreprowler
(70166, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What\'s this? A painting?', 47213), -- The Joy of Painting
(66218, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ta says all gnolls are dangerous and mean. But this is just a baby! \n\nMa says I always have to take care of Nau, and she\'s a baby, too.', 47213), -- Scampering Scamps
(70871, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Here\'s your Iskaaran fishing net. Use it wisely, and never take from the cycle of life more than you need to sustain yourself.', 47213), -- Iskaaran Fishing Net
(70129, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Goodness, what did you tell him? I\'ve never seen Rowie so spirited!\n\nThank you for bringing him home. I will do my best to take care of him in Kaqiata\'s place.', 47213), -- Toejam the Terrible
(66558, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks for helping me. You\'re nice.', 47213), -- Rowie
(71230, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My family is known as the best weavers of nets and crafters of harpoons. If you bring me the supplies I need, I can craft some new tools for you.', 47213), -- Tuskarr Fishing Gear
(70941, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hail, fellow fisher. \n\nI\'m almost hesitant to tell you of these serene fishing holes. But I must, because not doing so would deny you a bounty of fish and also the pleasure of a relaxing time fishing.\n\nIn telling everyone I worry about crowding my fishing spot, but I\'ll admit I can only take so much of the quiet. A good conversation with fishing friends is an even better way to relax than fishing alone!', 47213), -- Fishing Holes
(70939, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do you wanna be a great big soup master, too? \n\nI can\'t wait until I can see over the lip of the big pot! Then I\'ll finally be big enough to lead a feast!\n\nHere, this is for you! It\'ll help you on your soupy journey! Let me know if you wanna trade for anything else!', 47213), -- Cooking Utensils
(67175, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We did the right thing today. There will be more magical oddities to research, but this girl will not get more gifts from her lost father.', 47213), -- How To Stop An Exploding Toy Boat
(67177, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fine work! We\'ll put this aside for our future building plans. \n\nIt is concerning Gorger and its kind have migrated down here, but we will make the best of it.', 47213), -- WANTED: Gorger
(67174, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A toy boat that\'s a magical time bomb?\n\nOh boy.', 47213), -- Arcane Detection
(66227, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, that will do nicely! Thank you, adventurer.', 47213), -- Some Good Fishing
(66556, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I told ye I had the cave part right. Now we can see about establishin\' some proper diplomatic relations.', 47213), -- Ice Cave Ya Got There
(66555, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now to translate this mess...', 47213), -- Bear With Me
(66554, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hopefully ye didn\'t go too hard on \'em.', 47213), -- Aggressive Self-Defence
(66553, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, what did ya find?', 47213), -- Hollow Up
(66622, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n! I\'ll *hic* always remember your heroism!', 47213), -- Wayward Tools
(70627, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Regretfully, friend... I\'ve got bad news for ya about the Winterpelt furbolg.', 47213), -- What of the Winterpelt Clan?
(66152, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our clan has been clawed to shreds.\n\nI hope another will accept us.', 47213), -- Nowhere to Go
(66151, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My chieftain, I am sorry.\n\nThere was nothing else that could be done.', 47213), -- His Stone Heart
(66149, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will never forgive the Primalists for making our clan suffer.', 47213), -- Elemental Influence
(66148, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am sorry you met the Rustpine clan now. This is not my people.', 47213), -- Former Furbolg Family
(66150, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So many of my clan have fallen in battle with their brothers and sisters... all for the promise of power.\n\n<Radza utters a guttural growl which fades into a long, mournful whisper.>', 47213), -- Rescuing Radza
(66141, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My brother spoke the truth.\n\nIt is even worse than when I left.', 47213), -- Broken Traditions, Broken Bodies
(66429, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It was only at the very end that I began to appreciate Lathos. I took his patience and experience for granted.\n\nWe owe him our lives.\n\n<Rannan looks towards the Ruins of Karnthar.>\n\nI will never forget him.', 47213), -- I Will Remember
(66428, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Just like that he\'s... gone?\n\nHe gave his life to save us because the R.A.... the machine didn\'t work.\n\nLathos believed in me... I should have listened... I let him down...', 47213), -- Friendship For Granted
(66427, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is done then.\n\nNow it is all on Rannan. I trust his abilities. They have gotten us this far...', 47213), -- A Looming Menace
(66426, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is worse than we thought. The arcane energy is almost at its peak.\n\nSomething is hastening the process.', 47213), -- Running Out of Time
(66425, 378, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done it $p!\n\nWell, you and the R.A.D.D.E.R...\n\nBut whatever... Now, help me get Lathos back to Camp Nowhere.', 47213), -- Arcane Overload
(66423, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is... not good news.\n\nIf Sindragosa could not control Karnthar and ordered this station abandoned, I can only imagine the nefarious things that the Sundered Flame could do with it.\n\nWe must not let it fall into their hands.', 47213), -- Worries and Validations
(66422, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These Sundered Flame did not die by my hand... or by Rannan\'s \"signature move.\" \n\nThey were dead when we arrived. \n\nRannan believes they suffered multiple traumatic wounds caused by arcane energy.\n\nI agree with his observations. But it\'s unclear if it was the dragon console discharging or friendly fire...', 47213), -- The Expedition Continues!
(66353, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hm... You dispelled the anomalies, but the R.A.D. still detects an arcane surge... and it\'s rising by the minute.\n\nThat... can\'t be a good thing.', 47213), -- R.A.D. Anomalies
(66352, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $p. I am humbled by your skill and efficiency.\n\nMaybe I\'m not the only one who will be a \"good influence\" on Rannan.\n\nNow... let us find out what the Sundered Flame is doing here.', 47213), -- What the Enemy Knows
(66391, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You missed it! We walked RIGHT into a Sundered Flame patrol. \n\nLathos SLASHED through them, but there were too many!\n\nSo, I started casting arcane explosions left and right... KAPOW! ZING!\n\nOh, but um, yes... the energy surge...', 47213), -- To the Ruins!
(65834, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Aye, that should throw a wrench intae their plan.\n\nNow... just tae push... a... lil\'... harder...', 47213), -- Kill the Queen
(65832, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank Magni! This\'ll keep me blood from freezin\' long enough for the ice tae melt.', 47213), -- Dwarven Antifreeze
(65833, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Serves \'em right.\n\nThank ye, $n.', 47213), -- Primalist Tampering
(65758, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good tae see another face with the right number o\' eyes!', 47213), -- Grungir the Explorer
(65750, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'An unfortunate necessity. We could not allow them to spread.\n\nI think we\'ve learned all we can from them.', 47213), -- Eight-Legged Menace
(65769, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. I feared I would never see any of them again.', 47213), -- Icy Webs
(71093, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Infinite dragons? Their kind always has some kind of plan.\n\nI will inform the Dragon Queen that she will have to find some other way to restore the power of the Aspects.', 47213), -- Legacy of Tyr: Secrets of the Past
(70930, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A \"Coldsnap Sagittate\"? Hmm...', 47213), -- All Tea, No Shadeleaf
(70847, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s still intact. Hopefully it brings the next owner more luck.', 47213), -- Ancient Obsidian Charm
(72456, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent! I am certain both Wrathion and Sabellian will be pleased with your efforts.', 47213), -- Tomes Of Trust
(65421, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice climbing! Yips owes ye a drink or two!\n\nOh, the elementals? Nah, don\'t worry \'bout \'em. This is OUR adventure!\n\n<Rocky resumes gleefully shooting bullets through the air elementals.>', 47213), -- Climb Every Mountain
(66351, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ye\'re just in time. Pathfinder Yip is starting to lose her grip up there!', 47213), -- Smoke Over the Mountain
(70965, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Whew, glad I don\'t have to wear this heavy thing!\n\nI\'ll ensure this is properly documented, researched, and archived for the expedition.', 47213), -- -Unknown-
(66524, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are wonderful! Just wonderful! Say, have you done this before?', 47213), -- Amateur Protography
(70335, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your help is greatly appreciated! As a show of our gratitude, I want to offer you one of my special excavation tools. I also have all of these available for trade, so come and see me again if you wish to complete the set. \n\nThank you adventurer!', 47213), -- Simple Excavation Tools
(72524, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This basic equipment will get you started.\n\nCome back when you have more Dragon Isles Supplies to get trained in new gear.', 47213), -- Basic Climbing Gear
(70812, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A good cloak can be the most essential piece of gear on an expedition. Your help\'s earned you your choice of cloak. See me if you want to trade for a different one.', 47213), -- Expedition Cloaks
(70813, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Most of the treasure around here is in the ground--ancient artifacts, maybe even valuables. You\'re going to need a good shovel to get to it, though. Lucky you, I\'ve got an official expedition shovel with your name on it. Look for disturbed dirt, and see what you can find.', 47213), -- Digging Up Treasure
(69855, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You look like you\'ve got the strength, but I wonder if you\'ve got the gumption...', 47213), -- A Climber's Calling
(66658, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I would never have expected such help from an outsider before. You have my thanks.', 47213), -- The Nokhud Offensive: Founders Keepers
(72137, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My friend, get this thing away from me. Trade for it. Please. They call it a \"Hoofhelper\" but it\'s really just a nuisance. Always getting in the way. Not nearly big enough to be useful yet. I want it gone.\n\nWhat? No, I can\'t just give it to you. My wife would never forgive me.', 47213), -- Hatchling Plans
(70541, 378, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Treat your hunting companion with loyalty and respect and they will protect your life with their own.\n\nReturn when your renown grows and I will train you further.', 47213), -- Hunting Tactics: Companion
(66711, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, this will be helpful.\n\nIt is hard for me to rely on outsiders for such a key resource, but I cannot think of an alternate route.', 47213), -- Delicacy in the Dark
(65784, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fine creatures. We will make use of everything they have to offer.', 47213), -- -Unknown-
(66862, 11, 5, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, '<Theldren nods coldly at your offering.>\n\nExcellent work, $n.\n\nAll who enter shall see these fangs upon our shelf and fear the wrath brought upon those who would stand against the dragon flights.', 47213), -- -Unknown-
(70745, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am glad this will finally start to get better! We all deserve a little bit of downtime.\n\nI hope you find a short respite here as well: you have earned it, $n.', 47213), -- Enforced Relaxation
(66871, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 'This... Where did you get this, $n?\n\n<Reaches for the plume, carefully accepting the gift.>\n\nWe\'ll be sure this is given the attention it deserves.', 47213), -- -Unknown-
(70887, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My smaller kin are now able to freely explore the Dragon Isles. It pleases me to see them flourishing and enjoying new experiences.\n\nAllow me to show you more ways that they can express themselves to you and others.', 47213), -- Feeling Freedom
(72259, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As you bring me more artifacts, our knowledge of the Incarnates and their time period increases.  \n\nYou have my thanks. As a member of the Dragonscale Expedition, I want you to know how important your contributions are. And as a researcher, I want you to know the wealth of discoveries I have made from the artifacts you have brought me is a long-time dream come true. \n\nPlease, take these supplies and use them well.', 47213), -- Vault Artifacts
(72261, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Incarnates were locked away in the Vault, but aside from that we know very little either about it or its prisoners.\n\nArtifacts like this can shed light on their culture, their history, and... their power. Studying them could improve our odds in defeating the primalists. Bring me more of these I will reward you with supplies.\n\nOh, and I will pen a note to Caretaker Jakes reminding her of your continued assistance of the Dragonscale Expedition.', 47213), -- More Than a Prison?
(72354, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you were able to open it after all? Even those ancient magics recognize your knack for heroic exploits. \n\nIt would be wise to check the vault regularly. No doubt the treasures that lie within will prove useful in the battles to come.', 47213), -- The Great Vault
(72268, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, another adventurer! We could use your aid.', 47213), -- Azure Span
(72293, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Your decision has been made. You can return to the scouting map at any time to choose another location.>', 47213), -- Adventuring in the Dragon Isles
(70743, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Elzara ignores you and looks at Baby.>\n\nAre you safe, my precious cuddlemuffin?\n\nDid the Primalists bleed on you? How dare they!\n\n<Elzara notices you.>\n\nI shall definitely be rating this spa at one star. I expect a blood-free experience.', 47187), -- Precious Baby
(70744, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I do not want to know, do I?', 47187), -- Look at the Bones!
(70377, 432, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My sunglasses?! You expect a reward, I gather. You know the least you could have done is clean them.\n\n<Zeldis breathes on them, then wipes them off.>\n\nI suppose I can throw a few small coins your way.', 47187), -- Derelict Fashion
(70738, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hopefully this experience won\'t tarnish their reviews!', 47187), -- The You-ga Class
(70740, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A good start, but there are still far too many for my liking...', 47187), -- Steam Cleaning
(72728, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I heard about all the things you did! If that\'s not tough, I don\'t know what is.\n\nKeep up the pace.', 47187), -- The World Awaits
(71242, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, marvelous! This is just what we were looking for, thank you.', 47187), -- Supporting the Storm Researchers
(70753, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This will help further our research on the Primalists. Thank you.', 47187), -- Dissipating the Air Primalists
(72686, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is but a drop in the bucket. \n\nYou would do well to continue to slay the imbued creatures and prevent them growing in strength.\n\nNow I must return to my studies, $n.', 47187), -- Storm Surge
(67073, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Razageth and her allies must be stopped!', 47187), -- Red Dawn
(66675, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What happened, $n? Where is Alexstrasza?', 47187), -- Aspect Power
(70437, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This space seems clear enough.', 47187); -- To Tyrhold
